    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Treasuries yield flat, peg steady",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka Central Bank\u2019s guidance peg for interbank transactions weakened by five cents on Tuesday, while yields in Treasury Bonds T-bill remain steady in dull trade, dealers said.",
        "A bond maturing on 01. 06. 2025 closed at 28.00/28.25 percent on Friday, slightly up from 27.95/28.05 percent on Tuesday.",
        "Three months\u2019 bill was closed at 29.00/30 percent on Tuesday.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank announced a guidance peg for interbank transactions further weakened by five cents to 361.00 rupees against the US dollar on Tuesday from 360.95 rupees.",
        "Data showed that commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers between 368.00 and 370.00 for small transactions.\u00a0 (Colombo/ Aug 23/2022)"
      ],
